Active Directory User Onboarding Automation (PowerShell)

Overview

Manual user onboarding in Active Directory is time-consuming and prone to errors.
This project automates the provisioning of users with consistent configuration, validation, and logging.

Features:
-Automated user creation in Active Directory
-Role-based OU placement and group assignment
-Username collision handling (e.g., jdoe → jdoe1)
-Input validation for required fields and departments
-Idempotent design (safe to re-run without duplicates)
-Dry-run mode for testing without changes
-Logging and CSV reporting for auditability

How It Works:
-Reads user data from CSV
-Validates required fields and department mappings
-Generates unique username
-Creates user in appropriate OU
-Assigns group membership based on department
-Logs results and exports report

Example Input:
FirstName,LastName,Department
John,Doe,IT
John,Doe,IT
Jane,,HR
Bob,Smith,Finance

Example Output:
"Name","Username","Status","Message"
"John Doe","jdoe","Created","Success"
"John Doe","jdoe1","Failed","An attempt was made to add an object to the directory with a name that is already in use"
"Jane ","N/A","Failed","Missing required fields"
"Bob Smith","N/A","Failed","Invalid department"
